1 olive oil
1 tin sweetcorn
½ lemon
1 packet salmon
1 packet garlic paste
25 g butter
1 bag Slaw Mix
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 packet Smokey Aioli

• Drain the sweetcorn. Slice lemon into wedges.
• Heat a large frying pan over high heat. Cook corn until lightly browned, 4-5 minutes. Transfer to a large bowl.

TIP: Cover the pan with a lid if the kernels are “popping” out.

• Return the frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• Pat salmon dry with paper towel and season both sides.
• When oil is hot, cook salmon, skin-side down first, until just cooked through, 2-4 minutes each side.
• Remove pan from heat, then add garlic paste and the butter, turning salmon to coat.

TIP: Patting the skin dry helps it crisp up in the pan!

• While salmon is cooking, to the bowl of charred corn, add slaw mix, baby spinach leaves, smokey aioli, a squeeze of lemon juice and a drizzle of olive oil. Season and toss to combine.

• Divide seared salmon and charred corn slaw between plates.
• Spoon garlic butter sauce over salmon. Serve with remaining lemon wedges. Enjoy!